This paper deals with the problem of communication over a network to generate dependent random variables, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the exchange of messages over the network, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The problem of generating dependent random variables is also relevant to statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the study of bounds on achievable rates, which is a topic in optimization and algorithms (cs.DS).
